fields.description: First grade students learning fundamentals of reading, writing, and mathematics.
Second grade students building on foundational skills with more advanced concepts.
Third grade students developing critical thinking and problem-solving abilities.
Fourth grade students preparing for intermediate academic challenges.
Fifth grade students mastering core subjects before middle school transition.
Sixth grade students preparing for middle school with advanced curriculum.
Professional educators dedicated to student learning and development.
School leadership and administrative staff managing operations and policies.
Parent community supporting student education and school activities.
Essential support personnel including cafeteria, maintenance, and office staff.
